This is not how I wanted this evening to go.

148
00:12:14,819 --> 00:12:15,778


149
00:12:16,193 --> 00:12:17,816
我知道你对今晚的预想
I know how you wanted this evening to go.

150
00:12:18,028 --> 00:12:19,106
相信我
Believe me

151
00:12:19,237 --> 00:12:20,268
现实比预想好一点
this is better.

152
00:12:21,239 --> 00:12:23,112
你现在为谁工作？
Who are you working for?

153
00:12:23,492 --> 00:12:25,068
莱曼托夫吗？
Lermentov, yes?

154
00:12:27,037 --> 00:12:28,495
他觉得
Does he think

155
00:12:29,122 --> 00:12:30,913
我们需要他的允许
we have to go through him

156
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:32,665
才能运走我们的货物？
to move our cargo?

157
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:38,461
我还以为索罗霍布将军负责出口生意呢
I thought General Solohob is in charge of the export business.

158
00:12:38,799 --> 00:12:40,755
索罗霍布
Solohob

159
00:12:40,967 --> 00:12:43,006
只是中间人罢了
a bagman, a front.

160
00:12:45,472 --> 00:12:49,634
过时的情报害了你
Your outdated information betrays you.

161
00:12:51,228 --> 00:12:53,978
大名鼎鼎的黑寡妇
The famous Black Widow

162
00:12:55,649 --> 00:13:00,025
也不过是个漂亮的花瓶
and she turns out to be simply another pretty face.

163
00:13:00,904 --> 00:13:04,070
你真觉得我很漂亮？
You really think I'm pretty?

164
00:13:06,618 --> 00:13:08,859
告诉莱曼托夫我们货物的运输
Tell Lermentov we don't need him

165
00:13:09,162 --> 00:13:12,744
还轮不到他来插手
to move the tanks.

166
00:13:13,708 --> 00:13:16,329
他已是明日黄花了
Tell him he is out.

167
00:13:16,753 --> 00:13:18,377
不过
Well...

168
00:13:21,258 --> 00:13:23,000
你也许只能用写的了
...you may have to write it down.

169
